            <thetext>To retrieve the values of the found groups in regular expressions we most time use RegExp.$1, RegExp.$2. This can result easily into errors when a another regular expression is executed before the group values from the first regular expression are retrieved (as RegExp.$1 will return the result of the second regular expression).

Use the var matches = RegExp(&quot;&quot;).exec method instead and retrieve the found groups from the returned value (e.g. matches[1]).</thetext>
